Text: I am like a baby learning how to crawl, stand, and run in R shiny.
I have to admit that I still felt frustrated at week 4.
I know what I have to do, but could not get the result what I expected.
Especially when my team mates have been doing really great jobs, I surely have been under a lot of strain recently.
However, I so far enjoy exploring in R coding world.

Most importantly, I comprehend one thing, that is, always learn like babies, they do not afraid of failures, before they learn how to stand who fell down like thousand times, it seems like they do not know what is giving up, they try until they succeed.
